videos.description: Travis Etienne powers up the middle for a 4-yard touchdown run to get Clemson on the board early.
videos.headline: Clemson rips downfield for TD on first drive

videos.description: Ray-Ray McCloud trips and can't handle the punt by Miami and Trent Harris is there to recover for Miami.
videos.headline: Clemson muffs punt, turnover chain is dawned

videos.description: Kelly Bryant scrambles out of the pocket and is able to charge in to the end zone from 11 yards out for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Bryant scoots in for 2nd Clemson rushing TD

videos.description: Clemson chooses Adam Choice to run it in on the 1-yard line to add to their lead in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Choice rushes in for TD untouched

videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt says the 21-point deficit isn't insurmountable, but will take minor fixes at half to overcome.
videos.headline: Richt: 'Got another 30 minutes'

videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney says that the first half from Clemson was impressive, but they won't let up on Miami in the second half.
videos.headline: Swinney: 'That's a heck of a half'

videos.description: The Tigers run all over the Hurricanes in the first half, with three scores on the ground.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Clemson dominates first half) 2017/12/2 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: Clemson dominates first half

videos.description: Jeff Thomas tries to add some yards after his catch, but Ryan Carter punches the ball free and Clem Dorian is there for the recovery for the Tigers.
videos.headline: Clemson forcing the turnovers

videos.description: Malik Rosier's pass to Darrell Langham slips through his hands and into the diving arms of Ryan Carter, who also forced a fumble on the previous possession.
videos.headline: Clemson's Carter is a turnover machine

videos.description: Tavien Feaster keeps his feet moving and bounces out of the pile and in to the end zone as Clemson continues shut down of Miami.
videos.headline: Clemson is 'feasting' on the Hurricanes with 4th rushing TD

videos.description: Malik Rosier has his pass batted at the line and Kendall Joseph returns the interception all the way down to the 13-yard line.
videos.headline: Miami should turn over their chain to Clemson after 3rd turnover

videos.description: Kelly Bryant throws a perfect ball down the sideline to Deon Cain for the 27-yard touchdown as Miami's struggles continue.
videos.headline: Bryant tosses TD after INT

videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney couldn't be happier for his team and his seniors for pulling out the big victory against Miami in the ACC Championship.
videos.headline: Swinney: 'We're a program that feels we have a chance every year'

videos.description: Clemson head coach Dabo Swinney gets doused in orange Gatorade after Clemson closes out their third straight ACC Championship.
videos.headline: Dabo looks good in orange

videos.description: Christian Wilkins and Kelly Bryant explain why Clemson's third straight ACC Championship was no fluke.
videos.headline: Wilkins on Clemson's win: 'It's in our DNA'

videos.description: Clemson's defense comes to play forcing three turnovers as the offense has four TD runs in a 38-3 win over Miami.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Clemson shuts down Miami to take ACC crown) 2017/12/2 ESHEET SCEU

videos.headline: Clemson shuts down Miami to take ACC crown

videos.description: Head coach Dabo Swinney holds the trophy for the third time in as many years with promises of being No. 1 in the College Football Playoff.
videos.headline: Clemson crowed kings of ACC for third straight year

videos.description: Kelly Bryant passes for over 250 yards and a touchdown while running for another on his way to being named MVP of the game.
videos.headline: Bryant wins MVP of ACC Championship

videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit and Chris Fowler discuss why the College Football Playoff committee is going to have a tough time deciding which team is ranked higher.

videos.headline: The debate: Ohio State or Alabama

videos.description: Kelly Bryant and No. 1 Clemson make easy work of Miami to claim their spot in the College Football playoff in a 38-3 win.
videos.headline: Clemson earns ACC title with win over Miami

videos.description: Go inside the Tigers' touchdown that put the game out to win the ACC title.
